---
import BaseLayout from '../components/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
    title="Data Center Myths Debunked | Water, Power, and the Facts"
    description="Get the real facts about data center water usage and power consumption. Spoiler: it's far less than you've been told."
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 border-b border-tech-blue/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-pine-green/80 to-tech-blue/80 z-0 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1558494949-ef010cbdcc31?q=80&w=2668&auto=format&fit=crop')] bg-cover bg-center z-0 opacity-20 mix-blend-overlay"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 lg:py-24 text-center">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-red-500/10 text-red-300 font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-6 border border-red-500/20">Setting The Record Straight</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight">Myth vs. Reality</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-200 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-light">
                When a new facility is proposed for a community, residents deserve honest, complete information. Let's look at the actual math behind the rhetoric.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-slate-50 relative">
        <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            
            <!-- Water Use Intro & Facts -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-6">The Water Reality</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-slate-600">The total freshwater consumption of all U.S. data centers in 2023 was <strong class="text-tech-blue font-bold px-1 bg-tech-blue/10 rounded">less than 0.5%</strong> of America's total use.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Side by Side Myth/Fact Layout: Water -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-0 overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] shadow-xl border border-slate-200 mb-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                    <!-- MYTH -->
                    <div class="bg-slate-100 p-8 lg:p-12 relative flex flex-col justify-center">
                        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5">
                            <svg class="w-32 h-32" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 9v2m0 4h.01m-6.938 4h13.856c1.54 0 2.502-1.667 1.732-3L13.732 4c-.77-1.333-2.694-1.333-3.464 0L3.34 16c-.77 1.333.192 3 1.732 3z" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <span class="inline-block self-start px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-700 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs rounded-full mb-6">The Myth</span>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4 tracking-tight">"Data centers will drain or deplete our local water supply."</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-500 font-medium">A common concern fueled by misleading comparisons lacking national context.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FACT -->
                    <div class="bg-tech-blue p-8 lg:p-12 relative text-white flex flex-col justify-center">
                        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-10">
                            <svg class="w-32 h-32" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12l2 2 4-4m6 2a9 9 0 11-18 0 9 9 0 0118 0z" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <span class="inline-block self-start px-3 py-1 bg-white/20 text-white font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs rounded-full mb-6 relative z-10">The Fact</span>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight relative z-10">They consume roughly 15x less water than we lose to leaky municipal pipes.</h3>
                        <p class="text-blue-100 font-medium relative z-10">Agricultural irrigation accounts for approximately half of all U.S. freshwater, over 100 times the amount used by data centers.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- Water Table -->
                <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto bg-white rounded-3xl shadow-md border border-slate-200 overflow-hidden">
                    <div class="px-6 py-6 border-b border-slate-100 bg-slate-50">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 font-sans">Annual U.S. Freshwater Use Comparison</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                        <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse">
                            <thead>
                                <tr class="border-b border-slate-200 bg-white">
                                    <th class="py-4 px-6 text-sm font-bold tracking-wider text-slate-500 uppercase w-1/2">Consumer</th>
                                    <th class="py-4 px-6 text-sm font-bold tracking-wider text-slate-500 uppercase w-1/2">Annual Usage</th>
                                </tr>
                            </thead>
                            <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 bg-white font-medium">
                                <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-900 border-l-[4px] border-emerald-500">Agricultural Irrigation</td>
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-600">~50% of total U.S. freshwater</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors">
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-900 border-l-[4px] border-slate-400">Municipal Leaky Pipes <span class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-normal block">(lost water)</span></td>
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-600">~3 trillion gallons per year</td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr class="hover:bg-tech-blue/5 transition-colors bg-tech-blue/[0.02]">
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-tech-blue font-bold border-l-[4px] border-tech-blue">All U.S. Data Centers (2023)</td>
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-tech-blue font-bold">~200–580 million gallons per day <span class="bg-tech-blue text-white px-2 py-0.5 rounded ml-2 text-sm">(&lt; 0.5% total)</span></td>
                                </tr>
                                <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50 transition-colors bg-slate-50/50">
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-900 border-l-[4px] border-purple-500">Training the Largest AI Model <span class="text-slate-400 text-sm font-normal block">(Grok 4)</span></td>
                                    <td class="py-5 px-6 text-slate-600">Less than 1 sq. mile of farmland uses in a year</td>
                                </tr>
                            </tbody>
                        </table>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <!-- Modern Cooling Note -->
                <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto mt-12 text-center">
                    <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
                        Furthermore, modern data centers are increasingly designed to <strong class="text-slate-900">minimize water consumption</strong>. Many new facilities use air cooling or liquid immersion cooling systems that require little to no water, or use reclaimed wastewater rather than drawing from local freshwater supplies.
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            <hr class="border-slate-200 max-w-5xl mx-auto my-24 lg:my-32">

            <!-- Power Use Intro & Facts -->
            <div class="mb-16">
                <div class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-16">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl lg:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight text-slate-900 mb-6">The Power Grid Reality</h2>
                    <p class="text-lg lg:text-xl text-slate-600">Data centers require significant electricity, but the narrative that they simply take power from the community without giving back is completely misleading.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Side by Side Myth/Fact Layout: Power -->
                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-0 overflow-hidden rounded-[2rem] shadow-xl border border-slate-200 mb-16 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                    <!-- MYTH -->
                    <div class="bg-slate-100 p-8 lg:p-12 relative flex flex-col justify-center">
                        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-5 text-amber-500">
                            <svg class="w-32 h-32" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                               <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <span class="inline-block self-start px-3 py-1 bg-red-100 text-red-700 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs rounded-full mb-6 relative z-10">The Myth</span>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-800 mb-4 tracking-tight relative z-10">"Data centers will drain our power grid and raise electricity bills for residents."</h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-500 font-medium relative z-10">An assumption that fails to account for how modern facilities generate and store their own energy.</p>
                    </div>

                    <!-- FACT -->
                    <div class="bg-amber-500 p-8 lg:p-12 relative text-white flex flex-col justify-center">
                        <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 p-8 opacity-10 text-white">
                            <svg class="w-32 h-32" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M4 4v5h.582m15.356 2A8.001 8.001 0 004.582 9m0 0H9m11 11v-5h-.581m0 0a8.003 8.003 0 01-15.357-2m15.357 2H15" />
                            </svg>
                        </div>
                        <span class="inline-block self-start px-3 py-1 bg-white/20 text-white font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs rounded-full mb-6 relative z-10">The Fact</span>
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 tracking-tight relative z-10">They increasingly build their own power and can supply the grid during peaks.</h3>
                        <p class="text-amber-100 font-medium relative z-10">Bidirectional flow allows battery storage systems to send massive amounts of power <em class="font-bold underline">back</em> to the local grid during emergencies.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 max-w-5xl mx-auto">
                    <div class="bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-3 text-amber-500" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M12 3v1m0 16v1m9-9h-1M4 12H3m15.364 6.364l-.707-.707M6.343 6.343l-.707-.707m12.728 0l-.707.707M6.343 17.657l-.707.707M16 12a4 4 0 11-8 0 4 4 0 018 0z" />
                            </svg>
                            Behind-The-Meter Power
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed font-medium">
                            Modern data centers install their own solar arrays, wind turbines, battery storage systems, and small modular reactors directly at the facility site. By generating their own power, they radically reduce their burden on the local grid.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="bg-white p-8 lg:p-10 rounded-3xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4 flex items-center">
                            <svg class="w-6 h-6 mr-3 text-tech-blue" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                                <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M8 7h12m0 0l-4-4m4 4l-4 4m0 6H4m0 0l4 4m-4-4l4-4" />
                            </svg>
                            Bidirectional Power Flow
                        </h3>
                        <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed font-medium">
                            Because data centers invest heavily in large-scale battery storage, they store excess power during low demand, and supply that stored electricity back to the grid during severe weather or peak demand, acting as a massive grid stabilizer.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mt-20 pt-10 border-t border-slate-200 flex justify-center">
                <a href="/bastrop-county-story" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 text-white bg-tech-blue hover:bg-slate-900 font-bold rounded-xl shadow-md transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-xl text-lg group">
                    Next: Read the Bastrop Story
                    <svg class="ml-3 w-5 h-5 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                        <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M14 5l7 7m0 0l-7 7m7-7H3" />
                    </svg>
                </a>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
